What version of the runtime are you using? N/A
On what operating system? Ubuntu Linux 10.4 32-bit
What browser are you using? 10.0.648.82
&lt;b&gt;Please include version information for both the OS and the browser.&lt;/b&gt;

&lt;b&gt;What steps will reproduce the problem?&lt;/b&gt;
1. Run google-chrome --no-sandbox
2. Enable Native Client in about:flags
3. Go to http://build.chromium.org/f/client/gallery/life/life.html

&lt;b&gt;What is the expected output? What do you see instead?&lt;/b&gt;

This should display a graphical representation of Conway's Life game.

Instead, it just shows the text &amp;quot;Conway's Life&amp;quot; &amp;quot;Use the mouse to paint extra life into the simulation&amp;quot; with no graphical screen below.  Note that it is possible to use a mouse to select the canvas region.


&lt;b&gt;Please provide any additional information below and attach any relevant&lt;/b&gt;
&lt;b&gt;source files.&lt;/b&gt;

After pressing Ctrl-R, the simulation correctly starts.

This bug should be resolved by next milestone, if, by nothing else, by putting in a comment that you may need to press Ctrl-R to refresh the screen.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2011-06-22T17:02:33.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2011-02-17T15:56:14.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:status>Obsolete</ns2:status><ns2:owner>
